# Editor / IDE
# .vscode/ is intentionally tracked — extensions.json, settings.json,
# and launch.json carry shared workspace config that should follow
# the repo (so future-Jake on a new laptop gets the same setup).
# Per-user VSCode state (history, cache, etc.) doesn't live in
# .vscode/ so this is safe to track wholesale.
.idea/
*.swp

# Claude Code scratch
.claude/worktrees/

# Electron-builder scratch
*.blockmap
